# LucidGate example list: headerregexplist
# Format: One request/response header rewrite per line: regexp => replacement. Empty replacement deletes the header. Framing headers are protected by LucidGate.
# Lines beginning with # are comments and are ignored by the loader.
# To activate a rule, copy one example, remove the leading # and adapt it to your environment.
# You can include another file with: .Include<relative-or-absolute-path>
#
# Commented examples:
# (?i)^User-Agent:.*Chrome.* => User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0
# (?i)^Cookie:.*tracking_id=[^;]+;? => 
# (?i)^X-Debug-Mode:.* => 
# (?i)^X-Experiment:.* => X-Experiment: stable
# (?i)^Referer:\s*http://(.*)$ => Referer: https://$1
# (?i)^Server:.*Apache.* => Server: LucidGate
# (?i)^X-Powered-By:.* => 
# (?i)^X-Unwanted:.* => 
# (?i)^Cache-Control:.*no-store.* => Cache-Control: private
# (?i)^Pragma:.* => 
